<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-27T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-27T19:36:00-05:00" n="938" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d938">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2943.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-27T18:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Emilio Vásquez Gómez, who is now in San Antonio, is apparently the leader
                            of the revolutionary movement directed against this Government. It is
                            evident that in our interests as well as in the interest of the Mexican
                            Government he should either be expelled from American territory or,
                            under a liberal interpretation of the present neutrality laws, subjected
                            to imprisonment. Either course would have a beneficial effect.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>